Description:
  Generate a skeleton for a mirrOS_api data source

Example:
  rails generate source SOURCE_NAME
  rails generate source SOURCE_NAME field_1:type field_2:type

  Available types:
    string
    integer
    float

This will create:
  sources/SOURCE_NAME
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/Rakefile
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/README.md
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/MIT-LICENSE
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/SOURCE_NAME.gemspec
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/Gemfile
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/app/assets/templates/settings.vue
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/app/controllers/SOURCE_NAME/application_controller.rb (optional)
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/app/jobs/SOURCE_NAME/application_job.rb (optional)
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/app/mailers/SOURCE_NAME/application_mailer.rb (optional)
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/app/models/SOURCE_NAME/application_record.rb
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/app/models/SOURCE_NAME/SOURCE_NAME_data.rb
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/bin/rails
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/config/routes.rb
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/lib/SOURCE_NAME.rb
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/lib/name/version.rb
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/lib/name/engine.rb
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/lib/name/fetcher.rb
  sources/SOURCE_NAME/lib/tasks/SOURCE_NAME_tasks.rake (optional)
